[{"id":"VR597538","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown. One figure is labeled Before and the other figure is labeled After. The figure labeled Before is a circuit with a voltmeter that is connected across the plates of a parallel plate capacitor. The distance between the plates of the capacitor is d. The After figure shows the capacitor only. The distance between the plates of the fraction is d over 2. The space between the plates of the capacitor in the After figure is shaded and labeled kappa equals 2 to indicate the dielectric material.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR597538.g14.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An isolated, air-filled parallel plate capacitor consists of two metal plates, each of area <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>A</mi></math></span></span>, separated by a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> with a potential difference <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V\"><math alttext=\"V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>V</mi></math></span></span> between the plates. The capacitor is disconnected from the battery. The separation is reduced to a distance of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction d over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction d over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span>, and a dielectric material of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"kappa equals 2\"><math alttext=\"kappa equals 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>Îº</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is inserted between the plates. What is the electric potential difference of the capacitor after the changes have been made?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR597538_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V\"><math alttext=\"V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>V</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 V\"><math alttext=\"2 V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>V</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction V over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction V over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 V\"><math alttext=\"4 V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mi>V</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction V over 4\"><math alttext=\"the fraction V over 4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>V</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":4}]